<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Providers
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The current provider supports raster XYZ tile services through <Code>MapTileLayer</Code>. You can use OpenStreetMap or another compatible tile service by setting <Code>Source</Code>, <Code>Subdomains</Code>, and <Code>Attribution</Code> according to the service requirements.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Future providers can build on the same Blazorise map concepts, such as <Code>Map</Code>, <Code>MapMarker</Code>, <Code>MapCircle</Code>, <Code>MapPolyline</Code>, and <Code>MapPolygon</Code>, while adapting the rendering details internally.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Attribution is optional in the API, but tile providers often require it. When using OpenStreetMap tiles, set <Code>Attribution</Code> to credit OpenStreetMap contributors.
</DocsPageParagraph>

